What are Sneakers?
Sneakers are footwear primarily designed for sports or physical exercise but have evolved into everyday wear due to their comfort and style. These shoes feature flexible soles made of rubber or synthetic materials and uppers constructed from leather or synthetic fabrics. Popular categories include basketball shoes, running shoes, cross-trainers, and lifestyle sneakers. Once confined to athletic performance, sneakers now represent a global cultural phenomenon blending functionality, fashion, and self-expression.

